@DATABASE "Bionic Commando 128K"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - B - Bionic Commando 128K"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - B
                   ====================================

                           Bionic Commando 128K
                           ====================


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(34690,0)"}          34690,0
@{"Infinite Time " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(34167,62)"}          49298,201
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(34741,255)"}          34741,x (x= 1-255)

                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I cannot test this POKE on the Amiga as this is a
                         128K only game, but once ZXAM 128 is released, I
                         will.
                               Rastan.

@endnode
